<div id="review_461674163" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/461674163" />
    <a title="Christopher Munroe" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/8231551-christopher-munroe"><img alt="Christopher Munroe" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1331953209p2/8231551.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/461674163?book_show_action=true">Nov 23, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Christopher Munroe" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Christopher Munroe" href="/user/show/8231551-christopher-munroe">Christopher Munroe</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer461674163" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10269385116766310602">My adventure outside my usual genre preference continues with this, a memoir style book set in Kuwait, dealing with drug addiction, mental illness and redemption.<br/><br/>This was a challenge for me to get into, as knowing nothing about Heroin, or how life is lived in Kuwait, and having only a passing knowledge of mental illness, I have no idea how realistically some of the elements here are presented. However, in spite of my ill-farmiliarity with the subject matter, I found this a strangely compelling r</span>
  <span id="freeText10269385116766310602" style="display:none">My adventure outside my usual genre preference continues with this, a memoir style book set in Kuwait, dealing with drug addiction, mental illness and redemption.<br /><br />This was a challenge for me to get into, as knowing nothing about Heroin, or how life is lived in Kuwait, and having only a passing knowledge of mental illness, I have no idea how realistically some of the elements here are presented. However, in spite of my ill-farmiliarity with the subject matter, I found this a strangely compelling read. The prose is an odd mix of blunt and evocative language that starts out off-putting but grew on me as the story progressed and I became more comfortable with the poetry of it crashing back down into the mundane. The transitions between chapters were occasionally jarring, and I was frequently wishing for more details of the events as they progressed, but really, if my biggest complaint about a book is that there wasn't more of it, clearly the author's doing something right.<br /><br />I received this book as part of a review swap with the author, and having finished it I'm glad to've picked it up, it has a lot of charm.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10269385116766310602" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


